19/02/2006
BAGHDAD, Iraq -- Two Macedonian nationals working for the German cleaning company Ecolog in Basra have been abducted and are being held for ransom, the Macedonian Foreign Ministry reported on Saturday (18 February).
They were taken hostage Thursday.
This is the fourth case involving the abduction of Ecolog staff.
In the previous instances, the hostages were released after ransoms were paid.
(Reuters - 19/02/06, Reuters, AP, AFP - 18/02/06)
